        "Data": [
          "<h2>What to Do</h2>\n  <p>Use the appropriate type for the desired action. For example, in C/C&amp;#43;&amp;#43;, only use unsigned types for values that could never be negative, such as height, width, or other numbers related to quantity. This will simplify your sanity checks and will reduce surprises\n related to unexpected casting.</p>"
